00:00:07.130 --> 00:00:11.650
Vessel sinks are freestanding bathroom
sinks that sit directly on a counter top

00:00:11.650 --> 00:00:12.879
or vanity.

00:00:12.879 --> 00:00:17.289
They are a beautiful and elegant
alternative to traditional sinks.

00:00:17.289 --> 00:00:19.919
Since vessel sinks sits on top of the
counter,

00:00:19.919 --> 00:00:24.019
the counter height must be lower than
traditional counters. The sink itself

00:00:24.019 --> 00:00:28.469
should be about thirty two to thirty six
inches above the floor for adults to

00:00:28.469 --> 00:00:31.489
comfortably access the sink.

00:00:31.489 --> 00:00:35.789
One of the main factors when buying a
vessel sink is which material it will be

00:00:35.789 --> 00:00:36.890
made of.

00:00:36.890 --> 00:00:40.840
Glass is the most common and versatile
vessel sink material

00:00:40.840 --> 00:00:44.300
because of the many colors they come in
and there ease of cleaning.

00:00:44.300 --> 00:00:49.150
Styles range from clear class to hand blown
masterpieces. It can feature different

00:00:49.150 --> 00:00:53.330
textures compliment different themes.

00:00:53.330 --> 00:00:57.470
Stone is the next most popular vessel
sink material.

00:00:57.470 --> 00:01:01.870
Stone sinks are usually cut from a
single block to avoid seams and because

00:01:01.870 --> 00:01:02.690
of this

00:01:02.690 --> 00:01:06.380
they do tend to weigh more and will
require more support.

00:01:06.380 --> 00:01:10.330
However their rustic styling and
various textures and colors make them a

00:01:10.330 --> 00:01:13.880
diverse option to compliment any bathroom.

00:01:13.880 --> 00:01:18.560
Stainless steel vessel sinks are not as
common as stone or glass, but they offer

00:01:18.560 --> 00:01:23.080
the durability of stainless steel and a clean modern aesthetic that will match

00:01:23.080 --> 00:01:25.490
the modern bathroom.

00:01:25.490 --> 00:01:29.420
The styling of the stainless steel may
limit their capacity to match different

00:01:29.420 --> 00:01:31.300
bathrooms.

00:01:31.300 --> 00:01:34.770
Vessels sinks are also available in a
variety of metals

00:01:34.770 --> 00:01:37.240
such as copper, brass

00:01:37.240 --> 00:01:40.460
bronze and nickel.

00:01:40.460 --> 00:01:45.760
These metals can complement different wood finishes and other details in your bathroom.

00:01:45.760 --> 00:01:50.490
Vessel sinks typically require different
faucets than traditional sinks.

00:01:50.490 --> 00:01:53.190
Not all vessel sinks come with faucets.

00:01:53.190 --> 00:01:57.150
So make you have a faucet that will work when choosing your vessel sink.

00:01:57.150 --> 00:02:01.860
When you have a faucet that works make sure the water flows into the bottom of the sink.

00:02:01.860 --> 00:02:03.730
It the water hits the side

00:02:03.730 --> 00:02:06.030
it can cause water to splash.

00:02:06.030 --> 00:02:10.590
With their eye catching design and
diverse styles vessel sinks can be the

00:02:10.590 --> 00:02:12.609
focal point of your bathroom.

